    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-04-18T01:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-04-18T01:00:00-05:00" n="59"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d59">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">710.0011 P.W./4–1845: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Briggs</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-04-18T13:00:00+07:00"
                            >April 18, 1945—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received—1:12 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>641. Chinese Military Intelligence reports that the long anticipated drive to
                    neutralize the advance Allied air base at Chihkiang in western Hunan (Embassy’s
                    633, April 14, 4 p.m.) is under way, Jap troops in force from Changsha–Hengyang
                    area having started a broad westerly movement as of April 15.</p>
                <p>Same source indicates that Jap drive toward Sian has halted, perhaps only
                    temporarily.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Briggs</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
